  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed HMO development, by reason of a deficiency in the number of kitchen facilities, inadequate provision of natural light and ventilation to the kitchens, and a lack of internal communal area, would constitute a substandard and unsustainable form of development, that would provide poor quality living conditions for future residents. The proposal would therefore fail to comply with Policies D4, D6 and T6 of the London Plan (2021), the Technical Housing Standards, Council's HMO Licensing requirements and the Mayor's Housing SPG. | The proposed rear/side extension would result in unacceptable impacts on the amenity of adjoining residential properties in terms of loss of daylight, an increased sense of enclosure and overbearing effects contrary to policy 7B of Ealing's Development Management DPD, and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft new Local Plan (Regulation 19) and policy D6 of the London Plan (2021)."
